entries.title: Perth man Lachie Hunt suffered motorbike accident in Bali after claims he'd been mugged
entries.description: Perth man Lachie Hunt spent six days in Kuta's BIMC Hospital with a broken leg, bleeding on the brain and a suspected fractured spine.

entries.title: Rupert Murdoch scraps plan to combine Fox and News Corp
entries.description: Rupert Murdoch has scrapped his plan to combine Fox Corp and News Corp, a deal that would have reunited two halves of the media empire he split nearly a decade ago.

entries.title: Director of Harry and Meghan's Netflix series claims Palace 'tried to discredit documentary'
entries.description: Director Liz Garbus claims Buckingham Palace tried to 'discredit' the bombshell allegations in Harry and Meghan's docuseries by claiming the filmmakers did not contact the royals for comment.

entries.title: Republican SLAMS Kevin McCarthy's bid to throw Ilhan Omar, Eric Swalwell, Adam Schiff off committees
entries.description: 'Speaker McCarthy needs to stop "bread and circuses" in Congress and start governing for a change,' Indiana GOP Rep. Victoria Spartz said in a statement on Tuesday.

entries.title: Concerns grow for siblings Hadley and Maylea after they vanished from Ross Creek in Victoria
entries.description: Siblings Hadley, 11 and Maylea, 8, disappeared on Wednesday January 18 from Ross Creek, 13km south west of Ballarat in Victoria.

entries.title: McConnell says McCarthy and Biden must solve debt limit crisis
entries.description: The longtime Senate Republican leader said any solution to the debt limit crisis must originate from the House, and urged new Speaker Kevin McCarthy to negotiate with President Biden.

entries.title: Beijing has filled Britain's homes with gadgets that China can use to spy on us
entries.description: Most of us find it alarming enough that internet service providers know which websites we visit, yet we seem happy to give up this data for the right to trawl through social media and shop online

entries.title: Wendy Sleeman missing: Gold Coast woman's home on fire as cops search for Jamie 'Slade' Murdok
entries.description: A desperate search is underway for Gold Coast woman Wendy Sleeman, 61, after her blood was found inside her burning home on Tuesday.

entries.title: March of the mega-cities: World's total will rise to 37 by 2050
entries.description: By 2050, it's predicted that 70 percent of the world's population will live in mega-cities, according to the Institute for Economics & Peace.

entries.title: New York City set to FINALLY break nearly year-long snowless streak
entries.description: New York City is finally braced for snow after experiencing the second-longest drought in its history. Meteorologists predict flakes will fall on Wednesday for the first time since March, 2022.

entries.title: Pressure grows on Jeremy Hunt to rescue Britain as national debt hits terrifying record
entries.description: Jeremy Hunt was facing mounting pressure to deliver a growth plan last night after the national debt hit £2.5trillion. The shocking figure equals 99.5 per cent of Britain's annual economic output.

entries.title: Australia Day: Homeowners urged to start paying Aboriginals 'weekly rent' for living on their land
entries.description: A proposal to help Indigenous people suggests all Aussie homeowners donate one percent of their weekly wages - every week.- in order to 'Pay the Rent' for the use of Aboriginal land.

entries.description: Incidents allegedly included vulnerable children being beaten, locked outside naked in freezing temperatures, having vinegar poured on cuts and being fed a spoon of chilli flakes.

entries.title: Decision to free Serial's Adnan Syed appealed by murder victim's family
entries.description: Hae Min Lee's family seeks to appeal a decision to drop all the charges against Adnan Syed, saying the hearing was conducted in private and they were not provided with evidence.

entries.title: Hawley introduces PELOSI Act - bill to ban stock trades by lawmakers and spouses
entries.description: Sen. Josh Hawley reintroduced a bill to ban members of Congress and their spouses from owning and trading stocks, and used the name of his legislation to troll former Speaker Nancy Pelosi.

entries.title: Tesla will build $3.5B electric semi-truck manufacturing facility in Nevada

entries.title: Stocks are about to crash as the 'perfect bull market cocktail' ends
entries.description: Gateway Credit Capital Chief Investor Tim Gramatovich, pictured,  has warned that stock prices are about to crash as the 'perfect bull market' conditions come to an end after four decades.

entries.title: Five students killed in fiery head-on crash on their way home from Bible college in Wyoming

entries.title: Former Secretary of State Mike Pompeo says US must give Ukraine 'military assets it needs'
entries.description: Former  Secretary of State Mike Pompeo has said the United States must provide Ukraine with the military equipment it needs to defeat Russia and insisted ongoing support is 'in America's best interest'.

entries.title: Lovesick barman tried to stab his boss's boyfriend to death after becoming infatuated with her
entries.description: This savage weapon was part of a cache of blades owned by a would-be killer barman. Alexander Cornell was convicted of attempted murder after he stabbed his boss's boyfriend.

entries.title: Alec Baldwin and wife Hilaria pictured out in Manhattan again after being charged with manslaughter
entries.description: Having promised to fight the charges to his dying breath, the actor and his model wife Hilaria, also 39, were seen together Tuesday for just the second time since the decision was announced.

entries.title: Moment hero bystander grabs Monterey Park shooter's illegal weapon after he killed eleven people
entries.description: The full footage of a heroic bystander risking his life to disarm the Monterey Park shooter, by grabbing his illegal semi-automatic pistol after he killed eleven people in a jealous rage, has emerged.

entries.title: Tyson Foods heir pleads guilty after he was caught sleeping in a stranger's bed while drunk
entries.description: John R. Tyson, 32, the great-grandson of the meat company's founder, agreed to pay $440 after passing out in the college-aged woman's bed in Fayetteville, Arkansas, in November.

entries.title: Walmart is raising hourly wages to $14 an hour - up $2 - for 340,000 workers

entries.title: Son, 16, and father, 45, both die in hit-and-run crash while on a countryside cycle

entries.description: The Monterey Park shooter, Huu Can Tran, was a man who had built up a collection of grievances against his ex-wife, as well as the owners and instructors of the two dance halls.

entries.title: Alice Springs baker says Anthony Albanese should sack NT Police minister as crime escalates
entries.description: Darren Clarke's bakery in Alice Springs, in the Northern Territory, has been broken into 41 times over three years. He has called on the government to tackle escalating levels of crime.

entries.title: EPHRAIM HARDCASTLE: Will Queen's biography be hit by Spare?
entries.description: EPHRAIM HARDCASTLE: Has Harry's betrayal of family secrets in Spare thrown a spanner in the works of the official biography of the late Queen?

entries.title: Suspect on the run over raid on Mark Cavendish's home 'evaded arrest by shaving his red hair'
entries.description: Suspected gangster, Jo Jobson, was reportedly spotted near his home just two weeks ago while police have worked tirelessly to track him following the attack on the Olympic cyclist.

entries.title: Australia Day public holiday: Sydney pubs avoid using the words for January 26 events
entries.description: Sydney pubs in Darlinghurst, Double Bay, Miranda, Cronulla and others are marketing their Australia Day functions as 'public holiday eve' events.

entries.title: Queen Consort's former bodyguard Mark Andrews is made King Charles' head driver
entries.description: Mark Andrews has protected the Royal Family for 20 years and was head of the Queen Consort's police protection team before he retired from the Met last year aged 40.

entries.title: Bill Gates $70 million Gulfstream N887WM at Sydney's Kingsford Smith on Australia visit
entries.description: The world's fourth richest man relaxed on Lizard Island on Queensland's Great Barrier Reef before flying to Sydney on his private jet and will travel to Melbourne later in the week.

entries.title: Model Jeremy Ruehlemann dead at 27, fashion designer Christian Siriano calls him 'One of My Muses'
entries.description: Model Jeremy Ruehlemann, who appeared in fashion designer Christian Siriano's runway shows and considered to be his muse, has died at the age of 27.

entries.title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: Give Ukraine tools it needs to finish the job
entries.description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: Thanks to the stirring courage of its troops and the help of Nato - galvanised into action by Boris Johnson - Ukraine has defied Vladimir Putin's invasion.

entries.title: Millions set to work for longer as ministers draw up plans to increase the retirement age to 68
entries.description: Million of Britons could work for longer under secret government plans to raise the retirement age to 68 by 2035, it has been revealed

entries.title: Jeremy Hunt is forcing 1.5m people into higher tax band through his stealth raid on middle earners
entries.description: A further 1,130,000 will have to pay higher rate tax at 40 per cent by 2027-28. Over 300,000 will also be pulled into a 45 per cent additional tax band. It comes after Jeremy Hunt's tax raid on middle earners.

entries.title: Supermarkets not suppliers are behind unfair food price hikes on the shelves, insiders claim
entries.description: Supermarkets are fuelling the cost of living crisis by pushing through unfair price hikes, industry insiders claim.

entries.title: Backpacker rages about 'skinny' expats using sexy pictures to apply for farm jobs
entries.description: Chloe Saffron Belle, wrote the scathing message to the Backpacker Jobs in Australia Facebook page on Sunday night, asking 'skinny + sexy = employable?'.

entries.title: Shocking video shows the moments a massive cliff collapses onto beach in San Dieg
entries.description: Stunning video captured the moment a massive section of a cliff broke off and fell onto a San Diego beach. According to a geology professor, the collapse is the biggest cliff failure in 40 years

entries.title: Lyme disease: Tick bite in India reduces Adelaide man Matthew Mason to bed-bound patient
entries.description: Adelaide man Matthew Mason, 37, has revealed the tragic story of his spiralling health, after he contracted Lyme disease a decade ago while travelling in a remote part of India.

entries.title: Winklevoss twins' crypto exchange Gemini will layoff 10% of its staff, citing 'bad actors'
entries.description: Cryptocurrency exchange Gemini is slashing 10 percent of its staff - the third round of layoffs within just eight months, founders Cameron Winklevoss and Tyler Winklevoss announced on Monday.

entries.title: House Democratic leader's daughter in court accused of graffitiing 'All cops are bast**ds'
entries.description: Riley Dowell, 23, appeared in court on Monday to face charges including assault and battery on a police officer and vandalizing a historic marker or monument. She was released on $500 bail.

entries.title: Japan aide gets told off by his mother... for putting his hands in his pockets
entries.description: It should have been one of the proudest moments of his political career. But one Japanese aide will remember his visit to the US President for the wrong reasons.

entries.title: Housebuilder pledges to ditch gas boilers for heat pumps in homes to reduce carbon footprint
entries.description: Housebuilder Redrow has said all its new detached homes will be fitted with a heat pump instead of a gas boiler - the first pledge of its kind in the industry.

entries.title: Perth bikie Samuel Willmott looking for pen pals while serving time in Bunbury Regional Prison
entries.description: The Rebels bikie has spent the last 13 months behind bars at Bunbury Regional Prison after he was sentenced over the theft of $500,000 cash from a Perth backyard

entries.title: Cosmetics that contain fungi are mushrooming! Brands favour unusual 'ingredient' in products
entries.description: Fungi is said to have unique qualities that bring benefits such as reducing inflammation, treating blotchy pigmentation and soothing the skin. It is predicted to 'take centre stage' in beauty this year.

entries.title: Urgent warning over $469 fine that comes into force TOMORROW
entries.description: Drivers are being warned to be extra cautious as police ramp up patrols ahead of Australia Day and major penalties come into force for the long weekend.

entries.title: Mum and her guide dog refused entry at barber shop in Jannali, Sydney over 'scared' worker
entries.description: A single mother-of-two who has 'very low' vision and relies on a guide dog to walk was refused entry at a Sydney barber shop because the shop owner was 'scared'.

entries.title: Jacinta Price slams Prime Minister Anthony Albanese over Alice Springs war zone
entries.description: Senator Jacinta Price has accused Prime Minister Anthony Albanese of being quick to fly overseas and pledge help to other nations while ignoring the 'war zone' in the crime-racked Northern Territory.

entries.title: Fox News analyst and self-declared enemy of woke Gianno Caldwell was asked to leave Miami restaurant
entries.description: A political commentator for Fox News claims to have been asked to leave a North Miami bookstore and restaurant, Paradis Books and Bread, while discussing politics with friends.

entries.title: League table shame of UK women's healthcare: We languish behind Saudi Arabia in global list
entries.description: The UK has ranked lower than most comparable Western countries, including the US, Australia, New Zealand, France and Germany, in the 2021 Hologic Global Women's Health Index.

entries.title: Killer of graduate Zara Aleena should have been recalled to prison six days before brutal slaying
entries.description: A Sexual predator described as a 'ticking timebomb' was left free to kill a law graduate due to a catalogue of blunders by probation staff.
